FBIS3-41788 "jptep001__l94026" JPRS-TEP-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Epidemiology 25 February 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA KYRGYZSTAN Health Ministry Announces Measures To Prevent Cholera OW0909140193 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1305 GMT 9 Sep 93 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0909140193 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Following item transmitted via KYODO] [Text] Kyrgyzstan's Extraordinary Epidemiological Commission has taken urgent measures to prevent the spreading of cholera. The Kyrgyz Ministry of Public Health informed Interfax that the threat of an epidemic is coming from neighboring Uzbekistan, Tajikistan and Kazakhstan. According to the same source, the republic's sanitary services will exercise sanitary control over the railways and motor transport. Commercial charter flights to Pakistan, India, Turkey and Iran have been canceled until October 1. Private vendors have been forbidden to sell drinks, ice-cream and food stuffs. Control has been toughened over the quality of drinking water and over the rivers, lakes, and canals. The Kyrgyz sanitary and epidemiological service reports that no cholera cases have been registered in Kyrgyzstan so far.
